WEBVTT

1
00:00:06.673 --> 00:00:09.676
<i>[indistinct chatter]</i>

2
00:00:16.058 --> 00:00:17.726
- What's up. Ghost Rider?
- You good?

3
00:00:17.809 --> 00:00:18.977
{\an8}- Never better.

4
00:00:19.061 --> 00:00:20.812
{\an8}- OK. kids. bye-bye time.

5
00:00:20.896 --> 00:00:23.023
{\an8}Thanks for the trip
down memory lane.

6
00:00:23.065 --> 00:00:24.441
{\an8}Um. where's Evans?

7
00:00:24.525 --> 00:00:26.693
{\an8}- Uh. I think
she's by the family room.

8
00:00:26.777 --> 00:00:28.320
- She is.

9
00:00:28.403 --> 00:00:29.821
- Hey. hey. hey.
where are you going?

10
00:00:29.905 --> 00:00:31.365
I'm not gonna scan
all this by myself.

11
00:00:31.406 --> 00:00:32.950
- Cruz has a question
on my cellulitis.

12
00:00:33.033 --> 00:00:34.535
I'll be right back.
- You better.

13
00:00:34.618 --> 00:00:35.827
- Two minutes tops.
- Where's Mel?

14
00:00:35.911 --> 00:00:37.329
Where's Donnie?

15
00:00:37.371 --> 00:00:38.789
They should be helping you.
- I don't know.

16
00:00:38.872 --> 00:00:40.541
- OK. day shift. listen up.

17
00:00:40.582 --> 00:00:42.668
We're doing really well.
but we still got a ways to go.

18
00:00:42.709 --> 00:00:44.753
And nobody's going home
until all these paper charts

19
00:00:44.836 --> 00:00:46.505
are digitized. including me.

20
00:00:46.588 --> 00:00:48.423
- And then we're free
to celebrate our freedom?

21
00:00:48.507 --> 00:00:49.550
- Exactly.

22
00:00:49.591 --> 00:00:50.759
- Well. can you kick some ass

23
00:00:50.842 --> 00:00:51.927
and get the staff to hurry up

24
00:00:52.010 --> 00:00:53.095
on the EHR home pages?

25
00:00:53.178 --> 00:00:54.846
- Where are Larry and Antoine?

26
00:00:54.930 --> 00:00:56.139
- Antoine's fighting
on the phone

27
00:00:56.223 --> 00:00:57.516
with his girlfriend outside.

28
00:00:57.599 --> 00:01:00.310
And Larry's on a cafeteria run.

29
00:01:00.394 --> 00:01:02.854
- Yeah. that tracks.

30
00:01:02.938 --> 00:01:04.982
- We've got five patients
in beds waiting to be seen.

31
00:01:05.065 --> 00:01:06.984
How do you want to play this--
man to man or zone?

32
00:01:07.067 --> 00:01:08.402
- The zone.

33
00:01:08.485 --> 00:01:10.070
Have Cruz and Ellis split up
the new five.

34
00:01:10.153 --> 00:01:11.446
You take North and Central.

35
00:01:11.530 --> 00:01:13.198
I'll take South and Trauma.
- Cool.

36
00:01:13.282 --> 00:01:14.241
Want to switch at 1:00 AM?

37
00:01:14.324 --> 00:01:15.409
- Why?

38
00:01:15.450 --> 00:01:16.577
- Variety is the spice of life.

39
00:01:16.660 --> 00:01:18.036
- I thought that was garlic.

40
00:01:18.120 --> 00:01:21.039
- Oh. sorry.

41
00:01:21.123 --> 00:01:22.916
[sighs]
I told you I'd be fast.

42
00:01:23.000 --> 00:01:25.043
OK. let's do this
and get out of here.

43
00:01:25.127 --> 00:01:26.169
- What's the hurry?

44
00:01:26.253 --> 00:01:27.421
Got some hay to pitch?

45
00:01:27.462 --> 00:01:28.839
- Ha.

46
00:01:28.922 --> 00:01:30.340
[bell chimes]

47
00:01:30.424 --> 00:01:32.092
Oh. shoot.
- What?

48
00:01:32.134 --> 00:01:34.720
- Uh. my ID badge is missing.

49
00:01:34.803 --> 00:01:35.762
- Oh. no.
The one you just got?

50
00:01:35.804 --> 00:01:37.097
How'd you lose it?

51
00:01:37.180 --> 00:01:38.098
- I don't know.
It must have come off.

52
00:01:38.181 --> 00:01:39.433
- Classic.

53
00:01:39.516 --> 00:01:40.851
Hope you remember
your login and password.

54
00:01:40.934 --> 00:01:41.977
- OK. Retrace your steps.

55
00:01:42.060 --> 00:01:43.437
Where'd you have it last?

56
00:01:43.520 --> 00:01:46.106
- Uh. I was with Ogilvie
in the Ambulance Bay.

57
00:01:46.189 --> 00:01:48.275
- Not with Colonel Mustard
in the library?

58
00:01:48.358 --> 00:01:50.319
- Who's--what?

59
00:01:50.402 --> 00:01:51.612
No.

60
00:01:52.904 --> 00:01:55.282
- The boy has no clue.

61
00:01:56.074 --> 00:01:59.620
[machine dinging]

62
00:01:59.661 --> 00:02:01.705
- Please don't do that.

63
00:02:01.788 --> 00:02:03.457
- Oh. ma'am. I gotta go.

64
00:02:03.498 --> 00:02:06.168
I sit here any longer.
I'm gonna get bedsores.

65
00:02:08.337 --> 00:02:11.298
I--I'm supposed to get
some CT results.

66
00:02:11.340 --> 00:02:13.759
Any idea how much longer
that's gonna be?

67
00:02:13.842 --> 00:02:16.178
- Shouldn't be much longer.

68
00:02:16.261 --> 00:02:18.805
- Where's that Nurse Vivi?

69
00:02:18.847 --> 00:02:20.474
- You don't want any of that.

70
00:02:20.557 --> 00:02:22.768
- No?
- No. she's out of your league.

71
00:02:22.851 --> 00:02:24.686
- What league do you think
I play in?

72
00:02:24.770 --> 00:02:27.481
- Uh. old timer's night.
- [laughs]

73
00:02:27.564 --> 00:02:29.149
Yeah. you're probably right.

74
00:02:29.232 --> 00:02:32.319
But some teams still appreciate
a veteran presence.

75
00:02:32.361 --> 00:02:34.488
- Well. don't say
I didn't warn you.

76
00:02:34.571 --> 00:02:36.281
You are here for your heart.
after all.

77
00:02:36.365 --> 00:02:37.783
- My heart's been
broken before.

78
00:02:37.866 --> 00:02:39.326
What's one more time?

79
00:02:39.368 --> 00:02:41.411
- Uh. she's engaged
to a jujitsu instructor.

80
00:02:41.495 --> 00:02:43.080
- With a bang.
not a whimper. baby.

81
00:02:43.163 --> 00:02:44.498
- [laughs]

82
00:02:44.581 --> 00:02:46.166
- And it's a cool bath
a couple times a day

83
00:02:46.249 --> 00:02:48.710
for two days. followed by
aloe vera to your skin.

84
00:02:48.794 --> 00:02:50.045
- OK. that's it?

85
00:02:50.128 --> 00:02:52.339
- And sunscreen in your future.

86
00:02:52.381 --> 00:02:55.342
- No. I'm never going outside
ever again.

87
00:02:55.384 --> 00:02:58.804
- I wouldn't swear off the sun
entirely. you know?

88
00:02:58.845 --> 00:03:01.306
But like most things.
moderation.

89
00:03:01.348 --> 00:03:02.599
- Hey. we're getting
kind of shorthanded

90
00:03:02.683 --> 00:03:03.975
scanning charts out here.

91
00:03:04.059 --> 00:03:05.352
When you finish.
can you come lend a hand?

92
00:03:05.394 --> 00:03:06.436
- Yeah. happy to.

93
00:03:06.520 --> 00:03:07.562
- Thank you.

94
00:03:09.564 --> 00:03:11.441
- And by happy to.
I mean there is nothing

95
00:03:11.525 --> 00:03:13.193
I would rather do less.

96
00:03:13.235 --> 00:03:15.821
- They keep you pretty busy.

97
00:03:15.904 --> 00:03:19.908
- Yeah. and today has brought
some new challenges.

98
00:03:19.991 --> 00:03:21.201
This is really putting a crimp

99
00:03:21.243 --> 00:03:23.495
in my 4th of July
evening plans.

100
00:03:23.578 --> 00:03:25.997
- You're going to see
the fireworks?

101
00:03:26.039 --> 00:03:29.376
- Uh. no. I was gonna maybe
meet up with this guy.

102
00:03:29.459 --> 00:03:31.002
though that's sounding
less appealing

103
00:03:31.086 --> 00:03:33.505
than the three Bs
at this point.

104
00:03:33.588 --> 00:03:35.173
- The three Bs?

105
00:03:36.133 --> 00:03:38.510
- Book. bath. and bed.

106
00:03:38.593 --> 00:03:40.971
- College kid with mono
and hemorrhagic tonsils.

107
00:03:41.054 --> 00:03:42.681
admit med-surge or observation?

108
00:03:42.764 --> 00:03:43.724
- Uh. observation.

109
00:03:43.807 --> 00:03:45.183
Bleeding stopped with TXA.

110
00:03:45.267 --> 00:03:46.560
She's had steroids.
so should be

111
00:03:46.643 --> 00:03:47.894
ready for discharge
in the morning.

112
00:03:47.978 --> 00:03:49.688
- Cool.

113
00:03:49.771 --> 00:03:51.398
How was your first shift back?

114
00:03:51.481 --> 00:03:54.067
- Uh. slow start.
finding my rhythm.

115
00:03:54.151 --> 00:03:55.360
- [chuckles]

116
00:03:55.444 --> 00:03:57.404
You a little rusty.
Rusty James?

117
00:03:57.487 --> 00:03:59.865
Now you won't have Motorcycle
Boy to big brother you.

118
00:03:59.906 --> 00:04:01.450
- Is that a "Rumble Fish"
reference?

119
00:04:01.533 --> 00:04:02.909
- Sure is.

120
00:04:02.993 --> 00:04:05.579
- And Robby is my big brother
in this analogy?

121
00:04:05.620 --> 00:04:06.830
- Bingo.

122
00:04:06.913 --> 00:04:07.914
- Yeah. I wouldn't say
he's been

123
00:04:07.998 --> 00:04:09.833
looking out for me exactly.

124
00:04:09.916 --> 00:04:11.251
I think he'd probably prefer

125
00:04:11.334 --> 00:04:13.003
not to see me at all
today. actually.

126
00:04:13.086 --> 00:04:15.922
- And you think that's
because he's mad at you?

127
00:04:15.964 --> 00:04:20.802
- I think he feels like
I let him down. because I did.

128
00:04:20.886 --> 00:04:22.971
- Jesus. with all
the martyrs around here.

129
00:04:23.054 --> 00:04:24.473
you'd think this was
a passion play.

130
00:04:24.556 --> 00:04:26.183
- What's your take?

131
00:04:28.185 --> 00:04:29.561
- I worked with that man
for 10 months

132
00:04:29.644 --> 00:04:30.771
while you were gone.

133
00:04:30.812 --> 00:04:32.439
He's not mad at you.

134
00:04:32.522 --> 00:04:35.609
He's mad at himself
for failing you. Rusty James.

135
00:04:35.692 --> 00:04:37.068
- Really?

136
00:04:37.152 --> 00:04:38.278
- [sighs]

137
00:04:38.361 --> 00:04:40.739
Just more
White Knight/White noise.

138
00:04:40.822 --> 00:04:42.324
That's how it is.

139
00:04:44.618 --> 00:04:46.203
- Share this video
with your friends if you can.

140
00:04:46.286 --> 00:04:47.537
Thank you so much.

141
00:04:47.621 --> 00:04:49.456
Be kind. be safe. be brave.

142
00:04:49.539 --> 00:04:50.624
- What you doing?

143
00:04:50.665 --> 00:04:52.000
- Dr. Robby. sorry.

144
00:04:52.083 --> 00:04:53.001
I was just--

145
00:04:53.084 --> 00:04:54.461
- One of your TikToks? Yeah.

146
00:04:54.544 --> 00:04:56.087
About those. listen.
I'm not so sure that--

147
00:04:56.171 --> 00:04:57.923
- No. no. I was just sharing--
- No. I get it.

148
00:04:58.006 --> 00:04:59.424
I just--you know.
we do have HIPAA laws here.

149
00:04:59.508 --> 00:05:01.092
We don't let anybody film--

150
00:05:01.134 --> 00:05:02.302
- I would never violate
any HIPAA laws. Dr. Robby.

151
00:05:02.385 --> 00:05:03.595
I swear it.
- I understand.

152
00:05:03.678 --> 00:05:04.596
Even still.
we're getting behind

153
00:05:04.679 --> 00:05:05.639
on scanning patient charts.

154
00:05:05.722 --> 00:05:06.640
So how about no TikTok

155
00:05:06.723 --> 00:05:09.559
on the company clock. Dr. J?

156
00:05:09.643 --> 00:05:11.478
- Dr. Robby. I think you're--

157
00:05:11.520 --> 00:05:12.938
- Out of touch? Probably.

158
00:05:13.021 --> 00:05:14.314
You wouldn't be the first
to accuse me of it.

159
00:05:14.397 --> 00:05:16.066
However. when I was
in medical school--

160
00:05:16.149 --> 00:05:17.943
- You didn't have cell phones
or TikTok

161
00:05:18.026 --> 00:05:20.487
or internet or ICE agents
coming in here

162
00:05:20.529 --> 00:05:22.948
and taking away patients
and staff.

163
00:05:24.741 --> 00:05:26.284
I get it.

164
00:05:30.121 --> 00:05:33.667
- We did have cell phones.
maybe not in the beginning.

165
00:05:38.338 --> 00:05:39.422
Where do you think
you're going?

166
00:05:39.506 --> 00:05:41.091
- Uh. home.

167
00:05:41.174 --> 00:05:43.426
- I kind of need you
to hang out a little longer

168
00:05:43.510 --> 00:05:45.345
and help digitize some of these
analog patient records.

169
00:05:45.387 --> 00:05:46.805
- Normally. I would. truly.

170
00:05:46.888 --> 00:05:50.892
But I gotta get home--
wife. baby. bed.

171
00:05:50.976 --> 00:05:53.019
- OK.
Go get some rest.

172
00:05:53.103 --> 00:05:54.187
You sure you're OK
to drive home?

173
00:05:54.271 --> 00:05:55.188
- Absolutely.

174
00:05:55.272 --> 00:05:57.190
Just enough in the tank.

175
00:05:57.232 --> 00:05:59.234
- Don't tell anybody
I let you go.

176
00:05:59.317 --> 00:06:00.527
- Deal.

177
00:06:00.610 --> 00:06:02.028
Safe travels.

178
00:06:02.112 --> 00:06:04.155
Be sure to send some pictures
from the road.

179
00:06:20.964 --> 00:06:22.716
- Fight over at
Zazu's Sports Bar.

180
00:06:22.757 --> 00:06:24.092
The two combatants
are pulling up soon.

181
00:06:24.175 --> 00:06:25.385
One's a stabbing.

182
00:06:25.427 --> 00:06:26.386
- Ellis. double trauma
coming in.

183
00:06:26.428 --> 00:06:27.429
Grab the easy one.

184
00:06:27.512 --> 00:06:28.555
Bring the stabbing to Trauma 2.

185
00:06:28.638 --> 00:06:30.015
We will get the room set up.

186
00:06:30.098 --> 00:06:32.559
- All right. Roger.

187
00:06:32.601 --> 00:06:36.855
- OK. darling. time for this
dinosaur to head to extinction.

188
00:06:36.938 --> 00:06:38.231
- Got us through
a real jam today.

189
00:06:38.315 --> 00:06:40.483
Can't thank you enough. Monica.

190
00:06:40.567 --> 00:06:41.735
- Nice place to visit.

191
00:06:41.776 --> 00:06:43.153
Wouldn't want to live here
anymore.

192
00:06:43.236 --> 00:06:44.988
- Oh. me. neither some days.

193
00:06:45.071 --> 00:06:46.239
- But hey. Virginia Slim.

194
00:06:46.323 --> 00:06:48.241
you've come a long way.

195
00:06:48.325 --> 00:06:50.493
Glad I was wrong about you.

196
00:06:50.577 --> 00:06:51.745
Keep training 'em up right.

197
00:06:51.828 --> 00:06:53.038
- I'll try.

198
00:06:53.121 --> 00:06:54.623
- OK. that's enough mush.

199
00:06:54.706 --> 00:06:56.583
Back to my life
of mahjong and margaritas.

200
00:06:56.625 --> 00:06:57.959
Bye. Evans.
- Get home safe.

201
00:06:58.043 --> 00:06:59.586
- I will. See ya.

202
00:06:59.628 --> 00:07:00.670
- Bye.

203
00:07:04.466 --> 00:07:06.134
[sighs] She's right.

204
00:07:06.217 --> 00:07:09.304
You are the mama bear glue
that holds this place together.

205
00:07:13.767 --> 00:07:16.186
Hey. you OK?

206
00:07:16.269 --> 00:07:17.687
- No.

207
00:07:17.771 --> 00:07:20.398
I'm sad or scared.

208
00:07:20.482 --> 00:07:23.944
or some fucking thing.

209
00:07:23.985 --> 00:07:25.737
I'm worried.

210
00:07:25.779 --> 00:07:27.822
- What's going on?

211
00:07:27.906 --> 00:07:29.449
- Robby. I got a bad feeling.

212
00:07:29.532 --> 00:07:31.284
He's...

213
00:07:31.326 --> 00:07:33.119
it's like I'm never going
to see him again after tonight.

214
00:07:33.161 --> 00:07:34.454
- Did he say something?

215
00:07:34.496 --> 00:07:35.914
- Yeah.
he said a lot of things.

216
00:07:35.956 --> 00:07:37.457
You should talk to him.
He listens to you.

217
00:07:37.540 --> 00:07:38.792
- He's a grown-up.

218
00:07:38.833 --> 00:07:41.127
He just needs to go
on a vacation.

219
00:07:41.169 --> 00:07:42.963
- Can't you at least try

220
00:07:43.004 --> 00:07:45.256
to get him to promise
to come back in one piece?

221
00:07:46.883 --> 00:07:49.094
- He doesn't like to listen.

222
00:07:49.177 --> 00:07:50.720
- So make him.

223
00:07:55.642 --> 00:07:57.018
- [sighs]

224
00:07:57.102 --> 00:07:58.103
- Fuck it. Check my DMs.

225
00:07:58.186 --> 00:07:59.437
She hit me up.

226
00:07:59.521 --> 00:08:01.314
Sure. baby.
I didn't even respond.

227
00:08:01.356 --> 00:08:03.024
[siren wailing]
- Scavenger hunt?

228
00:08:03.108 --> 00:08:04.025
- Yeah. something like that.

229
00:08:04.109 --> 00:08:05.110
You need a hand?

230
00:08:05.193 --> 00:08:06.611
- Nope. You do you.

231
00:08:08.905 --> 00:08:10.156
What do we got?

232
00:08:10.240 --> 00:08:12.158
- Barrett Dunkle. 34.
decent vitals

233
00:08:12.242 --> 00:08:14.494
given he has Old Glory
jammed in his chest.

234
00:08:14.577 --> 00:08:18.123
Satting 91 on 15 liters.
BP 132 over 87.

235
00:08:18.206 --> 00:08:19.791
tachy at 112.

236
00:08:19.874 --> 00:08:21.001
- Dr. Abbot's expecting you.

237
00:08:21.084 --> 00:08:23.503
- Whoa. whoa. whoa.
whoa. whoa. man!

238
00:08:23.545 --> 00:08:25.797
- What the fuck?
- I'll call you back. baby.

239
00:08:28.299 --> 00:08:29.217
- Shit.

240
00:08:29.300 --> 00:08:30.301
I thought I cleared it.

241
00:08:30.385 --> 00:08:31.302
Was it sticking out?

242
00:08:31.386 --> 00:08:33.138
- Sticking out. my ass!

243
00:08:33.221 --> 00:08:34.514
Man. this is on you.

244
00:08:34.556 --> 00:08:35.890
You went wide.
and you clipped the shit.

245
00:08:35.974 --> 00:08:37.517
- Bikes shouldn't be
parked there.

246
00:08:37.600 --> 00:08:39.227
It was sticking out. Had to be.

247
00:08:39.310 --> 00:08:41.521
- Ain't no fucking way.

248
00:08:41.604 --> 00:08:43.356
Oh. no. you paying for this.

249
00:08:43.398 --> 00:08:45.191
Either you or the city.
but you paying for this!

250
00:08:45.233 --> 00:08:46.693
- Seriously?
We don't need this hassle.

251
00:08:46.735 --> 00:08:47.819
- I know. I know.

252
00:08:47.902 --> 00:08:49.404
Fuck! How bad is it?

253
00:08:49.487 --> 00:08:50.405
- Not really good.

254
00:08:50.488 --> 00:08:51.573
- Fuck!

255
00:08:51.656 --> 00:08:52.657
- Is that you.
you motherfucker?

256
00:08:52.741 --> 00:08:54.325
- Yeah. you better believe it!

257
00:08:54.409 --> 00:08:55.827
I'm gonna take this thing
out of my chest

258
00:08:55.910 --> 00:08:57.704
and shove it up
your fucking ass!

