00:18:25.104 --> 00:18:26.772
- She's had four of morphine.

514
00:18:26.856 --> 00:18:28.274
How's the pain?

515
00:18:28.316 --> 00:18:29.567
- Down to an 8.

516
00:18:29.650 --> 00:18:31.027
- There it is. lateral STEMI.

517
00:18:31.110 --> 00:18:32.278
OK. call it in.

518
00:18:32.320 --> 00:18:33.946
- The leads were too low
to catch it?

519
00:18:33.988 --> 00:18:35.448
- Yeah. it's not the first time
it's happened.

520
00:18:35.531 --> 00:18:37.033
You get a male medic
who's more concerned about

521
00:18:37.116 --> 00:18:38.576
getting sued or a complaint
for undoing a bra.

522
00:18:38.659 --> 00:18:40.036
You see these
anterior leads here?

523
00:18:40.119 --> 00:18:41.454
- Code STEMI. South 15.

524
00:18:41.495 --> 00:18:42.788
- Edith. you're having
a heart attack

525
00:18:42.830 --> 00:18:44.290
from a blockage in the artery

526
00:18:44.332 --> 00:18:45.958
that brings oxygen
to your heart muscle.

527
00:18:46.042 --> 00:18:48.210
If we get you to the--
- Lateral STEMI. V-tach arrest.

528
00:18:48.294 --> 00:18:50.129
Got her back after one shock.
She needs the cath lab.

529
00:18:50.212 --> 00:18:51.839
- And serious heart damage.
- Oh. my God.

530
00:18:51.922 --> 00:18:54.634
- You're going to be OK.
- Hello. I'm Dr. Cruz.

531
00:18:54.675 --> 00:18:56.302
- And I'm Dr. Shen.
How are you feeling?

532
00:18:56.385 --> 00:18:57.762
- I'm really scared.

533
00:18:57.845 --> 00:18:59.472
- We've got you.
Anything else?

534
00:18:59.513 --> 00:19:01.515
- Uh. like I got kicked
in the chest.

535
00:19:01.599 --> 00:19:03.267
- Normal after
a shock to the heart.

536
00:19:03.351 --> 00:19:04.977
Family?
- Yeah. husband's en route.

537
00:19:05.061 --> 00:19:06.771
- Leave the defib pads on
and take her up in a minute.

538
00:19:06.854 --> 00:19:08.147
I'm gonna chaperone
a nerve block real quick.

539
00:19:08.189 --> 00:19:09.231
- Go.

540
00:19:11.233 --> 00:19:12.860
- Where's Dr. Al-Hashimi?

541
00:19:12.943 --> 00:19:14.820
- She was just here.

542
00:19:24.205 --> 00:19:26.332
- Hello. everyone.
I'm Dr. Shen.

543
00:19:26.415 --> 00:19:28.167
Heard a rumor someone
needed a nerve block.

544
00:19:28.250 --> 00:19:29.835
I'm guessing that's you.

545
00:19:29.919 --> 00:19:31.921
- Probably so. although.

546
00:19:32.004 --> 00:19:33.506
you know.
I don't have much pain.

547
00:19:33.547 --> 00:19:35.591
I guess it's my diabetes.

548
00:19:35.675 --> 00:19:39.136
- We still need to numb you up
to do a proper deep clean.

549
00:19:39.220 --> 00:19:41.013
- You guys do
whatever you gotta do.

550
00:19:41.097 --> 00:19:43.516
- Three shots. median.
ulnar. and radial.

551
00:19:43.557 --> 00:19:45.351
2 grams of Ancef.
100 milligrams of Gent

552
00:19:45.434 --> 00:19:46.602
for gram-negative coverage.

553
00:19:46.686 --> 00:19:47.978
How'd you do this?

554
00:19:48.062 --> 00:19:50.648
- Oh. a family reunion
tug-of-war.

555
00:19:50.731 --> 00:19:52.817
I wrapped the rope around
my hand for better grip.

556
00:19:52.900 --> 00:19:55.861
And when we fell down. those
bastards just kept pulling.

557
00:19:55.903 --> 00:19:57.363
- Dirty.

558
00:19:57.446 --> 00:19:59.865
- Nah. it's just--
just the way we play.

559
00:19:59.949 --> 00:20:02.702
[laughs]

560
00:20:02.785 --> 00:20:04.203
- Michael. you got a second?

561
00:20:04.286 --> 00:20:05.830
- Uh. not really. no.

562
00:20:05.913 --> 00:20:07.581
- Well. how about
showing me a little respect

563
00:20:07.665 --> 00:20:09.750
and finding one?

564
00:20:09.834 --> 00:20:10.876
- Sorry. Caleb.

565
00:20:10.960 --> 00:20:12.378
Are you feeling disrespected?

566
00:20:12.461 --> 00:20:14.380
- Given that you've been
actively blowing me off

567
00:20:14.463 --> 00:20:16.048
all day. yeah.
maybe a little bit.

568
00:20:16.090 --> 00:20:17.508
But I have a thick skin.

569
00:20:18.801 --> 00:20:20.386
- What can I do for you?

570
00:20:20.428 --> 00:20:23.264
- "Should have found
a higher place to jump from."

571
00:20:23.347 --> 00:20:25.683
It's an interesting diagnosis.
Doctor.

572
00:20:29.603 --> 00:20:31.230
No pithy retort?

573
00:20:31.313 --> 00:20:33.315
Yeah. I didn't think so.

574
00:20:33.399 --> 00:20:35.568
Uh. I just came to say goodbye.

575
00:20:35.651 --> 00:20:37.319
I'm leaving soon.

576
00:20:37.403 --> 00:20:39.113
I know you are too.

577
00:20:40.448 --> 00:20:42.116
- Yes.

578
00:20:43.409 --> 00:20:45.661
- Keep my number handy.
just in case. huh?

579
00:20:45.745 --> 00:20:47.663
- Yes. I promise I will.

580
00:20:47.747 --> 00:20:48.998
Thank you. Caleb.

581
00:20:51.459 --> 00:20:53.669
- We're gonna give you one
Diflucan pill to take home.

582
00:20:53.753 --> 00:20:56.547
Take it in three days
if your symptoms persist.

583
00:20:56.630 --> 00:20:58.299
- How do I get there?

584
00:20:58.382 --> 00:20:59.759
- Where's that?

585
00:20:59.800 --> 00:21:01.427
- Home.

586
00:21:01.469 --> 00:21:02.720
- Do you know where you live?

587
00:21:02.803 --> 00:21:04.597
- Of course I do. It's not far.

588
00:21:04.680 --> 00:21:07.057
But I don't have
a way to get there.

589
00:21:08.225 --> 00:21:09.810
- How'd you get here?

590
00:21:09.894 --> 00:21:12.146
- My--my neighbor Gwen
dropped me off.

591
00:21:12.229 --> 00:21:14.482
but she can't drive at night.

592
00:21:14.565 --> 00:21:17.234
- We could call you
an Uber or a taxi.

593
00:21:17.318 --> 00:21:19.904
- I don't have any money.

594
00:21:19.987 --> 00:21:21.572
- Excuse me.

595
00:21:21.655 --> 00:21:23.115
Can I help?

596
00:21:23.199 --> 00:21:24.825
- Mrs. Clymer has
been discharged.

597
00:21:24.909 --> 00:21:25.868
but has no way home.

598
00:21:25.951 --> 00:21:26.911
- I'm so sorry.

599
00:21:26.994 --> 00:21:27.912
I don't mean to be a burden.

600
00:21:27.995 --> 00:21:29.288
- No burden at all.

601
00:21:29.330 --> 00:21:32.208
Why don't we call you a Lyft?

602
00:21:32.291 --> 00:21:33.542
- What is that?

603
00:21:33.626 --> 00:21:34.877
- It's like a taxi service.

604
00:21:34.960 --> 00:21:36.712
If you put your address
in here.

605
00:21:36.796 --> 00:21:39.131
a car will arrive in a few
minutes to bring you home.

606
00:21:39.173 --> 00:21:40.424
- Oh.
- My treat.

607
00:21:40.508 --> 00:21:41.634
- [laughs]

608
00:21:41.717 --> 00:21:45.763
That's very kind of you. truly.

609
00:21:45.846 --> 00:21:47.306
- Perfect.

610
00:21:47.389 --> 00:21:49.391
OK. Olive. could you take
Mrs. Clymer out

611
00:21:49.475 --> 00:21:52.102
to the ambulance bay.
where Florian will be

612
00:21:52.186 --> 00:21:54.271
arriving in six minutes
in a white Toyota Camry?

613
00:21:54.355 --> 00:21:55.481
- You bet.

614
00:21:55.523 --> 00:21:56.816
- Thank you.

615
00:21:56.899 --> 00:21:58.984
- I could use some good karma.

616
00:21:59.026 --> 00:22:00.778
OK.

617
00:22:03.572 --> 00:22:05.825
Oh. uh. hey.

618
00:22:07.368 --> 00:22:08.661
- Relax. buddy.

619
00:22:08.744 --> 00:22:10.496
It's Advil.

620
00:22:10.579 --> 00:22:12.832
- No. I didn't think you were--

621
00:22:12.873 --> 00:22:14.166
[sighs]

622
00:22:14.208 --> 00:22:15.876
Headache?

623
00:22:15.960 --> 00:22:18.963
- Uh. I tweaked my back
a little

624
00:22:19.046 --> 00:22:21.799
lifting that overheated kid.

625
00:22:21.841 --> 00:22:23.133
I guess I should get used to

626
00:22:23.217 --> 00:22:25.845
playing through the pain
again. huh?

627
00:22:25.928 --> 00:22:28.347
You look like you got into
shape since I saw you last.

628
00:22:28.389 --> 00:22:30.307
Didn't peg you as a gym guy.

629
00:22:30.391 --> 00:22:31.684
- Oh. no.

630
00:22:31.767 --> 00:22:34.520
I'm maybe more of a barn guy.
[chuckles]

631
00:22:34.562 --> 00:22:37.565
I'm helping out a friend
on the farm. so...

632
00:22:39.233 --> 00:22:40.276
- Nice.

633
00:22:40.359 --> 00:22:41.986
I'm picturing "Babe."

634
00:22:42.027 --> 00:22:43.779
except instead of
Farmer Hoggett. it's you.

635
00:22:43.863 --> 00:22:45.155
And instead of a pig--

636
00:22:45.239 --> 00:22:47.074
- Can you cut the shit?

637
00:22:48.617 --> 00:22:49.952
- Excuse me?

638
00:22:50.035 --> 00:22:52.204
- The sarcasm thing.
the--the--the--

639
00:22:52.246 --> 00:22:53.956
the little buddy routine.
like--like--like.

640
00:22:54.039 --> 00:22:55.833
you're what. you're
the Skipper. I'm Gilligan?

641
00:22:55.916 --> 00:22:57.710
Dude. you're not the Skipper.

642
00:22:57.793 --> 00:23:00.004
- I know I'm not the Skipper.
Robby is the Skipper.

643
00:23:00.087 --> 00:23:02.089
- No. Robby is the Professor.
Dana's the Skipper.

644
00:23:02.172 --> 00:23:03.674
- OK. somebody's watched
a lot of Nick at Nite.

645
00:23:03.757 --> 00:23:06.051
So who am I?

646
00:23:06.135 --> 00:23:08.220
- Play whatever part you like.

647
00:23:08.304 --> 00:23:10.598
Just don't pick mine for me.

648
00:23:12.099 --> 00:23:13.392
- OK.

649
00:23:13.475 --> 00:23:15.436
OK. that's fair.

650
00:23:15.519 --> 00:23:17.104
You got it.

651
00:23:17.187 --> 00:23:19.356
- Thank you.

652
00:23:19.440 --> 00:23:21.734
- You headed home?

653
00:23:21.817 --> 00:23:24.528
- Uh. no. I'm waiting on Robby.

654
00:23:24.612 --> 00:23:26.280
He asked me to house-sit
while he's gone.

655
00:23:26.363 --> 00:23:29.158
So I'm waiting for the keys.
the alarm code.

656
00:23:30.576 --> 00:23:31.911
- Nice. Nice.

657
00:23:31.952 --> 00:23:33.746
Yeah. I've--
I've seen his place.

658
00:23:33.829 --> 00:23:36.081
You're in for a sweet setup.

659
00:23:36.123 --> 00:23:38.167
- Cool.

660
00:23:38.250 --> 00:23:42.004
I'm sorry if I came across
a little strong.

661
00:23:42.087 --> 00:23:44.340
- Don't apologize
for standing up for yourself.

662
00:23:44.423 --> 00:23:46.342
It's a healthy habit.

663
00:23:46.425 --> 00:23:48.260
- [sighs]

664
00:23:48.344 --> 00:23:50.179
- You know. I really don't
need to see this again.

665
00:23:50.262 --> 00:23:51.680
- No. this is my favorite part.

666
00:23:51.764 --> 00:23:53.223
[laughs]

667
00:23:53.307 --> 00:23:54.266
- My hand's starting to cramp.

668
00:23:54.308 --> 00:23:55.517
We gotta be done soon.

669
00:23:55.601 --> 00:23:57.269
- Oh. you can be done now.

670
00:23:57.311 --> 00:24:00.356
But if you want to the hospital
to cover you. last one.

671
00:24:05.986 --> 00:24:08.989
- Hey. Robby.
It was an accident. man.

672
00:24:09.073 --> 00:24:10.574
- What are you talking about?

673
00:24:10.658 --> 00:24:12.743
- Your bike.

674
00:24:16.330 --> 00:24:19.375
[sirens wailing]

675
00:24:20.584 --> 00:24:23.087
- Son of a bitch.

676
00:24:23.170 --> 00:24:25.881
Oh. motherfucker!

677
00:24:27.341 --> 00:24:29.301
- Robby. GSW to the head.

678
00:24:29.385 --> 00:24:30.636
- Somebody hit my bike.

679
00:24:30.678 --> 00:24:32.179
- Dude. that sucks.

680
00:24:32.262 --> 00:24:33.722
Is it still rideable?

681
00:24:33.806 --> 00:24:34.974
[man singing
"My Country 'Tis of Thee"]

682
00:24:35.015 --> 00:24:36.600
- It better be.

683
00:24:36.684 --> 00:24:38.811
- Elbridge Gerry. 25.
stable with good vitals.

684
00:24:38.894 --> 00:24:40.437
- â™ª Of thee I sing â™ª

685
00:24:40.479 --> 00:24:41.981
- Was shooting his
.22 caliber pistol in the air

686
00:24:42.064 --> 00:24:43.482
with an aluminum pot
on his head for protection.

687
00:24:43.565 --> 00:24:44.817
Didn't work.

688
00:24:44.900 --> 00:24:46.235
- He's had about a quart
of Seagrams 7

689
00:24:46.318 --> 00:24:47.486
and will probably light up
a tox screen

690
00:24:47.569 --> 00:24:49.822
like a Roman candle.

691
00:24:49.905 --> 00:24:52.449
- â™ª We start fucking â™ª

692
00:24:52.533 --> 00:24:53.909
- Real wordsmith.

693
00:24:53.993 --> 00:24:55.327
- Entry wound
in the frontal scalp.

694
00:24:55.369 --> 00:24:56.662
seems to have tracked down
the forehead.

695
00:24:56.704 --> 00:24:57.788
As alert and oriented
as you can be

696
00:24:57.871 --> 00:24:58.998
after multiple bong hits.

697
00:24:59.081 --> 00:25:00.499
Got vital satting 98
on room air.

698
00:25:00.541 --> 00:25:01.834
- Sorry. Robby.
- Don't you fucking leave.

699
00:25:01.875 --> 00:25:02.835
- I can explain.
- I will be right back.

700
00:25:02.876 --> 00:25:03.836
- What's this?

701
00:25:03.877 --> 00:25:05.295
- Trauma 2.

702
00:25:05.379 --> 00:25:06.672
- Low velocity GSW to the head.

703
00:25:06.755 --> 00:25:08.132
seems to have
remained extracranial.

704
00:25:08.215 --> 00:25:09.675
- Lucky guy.

705
00:25:09.758 --> 00:25:13.846
- â™ª Gloria. Gloria.
here's a dollar! â™ª

706
00:25:13.887 --> 00:25:16.348
- After a fireworks
explosion resulting

707
00:25:16.432 --> 00:25:18.726
in the loss of two fingers.

708
00:25:18.809 --> 00:25:20.894
- Ooh. that sounds nasty.

709
00:25:20.978 --> 00:25:23.564
- Yeah. that was a sad one.

710
00:25:23.647 --> 00:25:24.982
Parents were deported.

711
00:25:25.065 --> 00:25:27.359
Big sister works
a full-time job

712
00:25:27.443 --> 00:25:28.902
and is the sole caregiver.

713
00:25:28.986 --> 00:25:30.571
- Been there. done that.

714
00:25:30.654 --> 00:25:32.364
- Your parents were deported?

715
00:25:32.448 --> 00:25:34.241
- Oh. no.
I thought she said departed.

716
00:25:35.868 --> 00:25:37.661
Did either of you guys work on

717
00:25:37.745 --> 00:25:40.497
the Revolutionary War
reenactors earlier?

718
00:25:40.581 --> 00:25:43.208
- Why. you didn't think you
could pull off a tricorn hat?

719
00:25:43.250 --> 00:25:46.045
- [chuckles]
Maybe.

720
00:25:46.128 --> 00:25:47.713
I've always loved history.

721
00:25:47.755 --> 00:25:51.717
and Colonial Williamsburg
was my favorite school trip.

722
00:25:51.800 --> 00:25:53.385
And. you know.
there's always the Ren Faire.

723
00:25:53.469 --> 00:25:55.846
but that's just once a year.

724
00:25:55.888 --> 00:25:58.182
How often do you think
the reenactors get together?

725
00:25:59.808 --> 00:26:01.560
- I don't know. No.

726
00:26:01.602 --> 00:26:03.395
- You should definitely
look into that.

727
00:26:03.479 --> 00:26:04.688
- Yeah?
- Yeah.

728
00:26:04.772 --> 00:26:05.981
- OK.

729
00:26:07.858 --> 00:26:10.903
[engine revving]

730
00:26:15.949 --> 00:26:18.077
- Deep-throated husky
with a touch of bitch.

731
00:26:18.160 --> 00:26:19.578
That's her tune.

732
00:26:19.620 --> 00:26:20.913
- That's what I thought.
but you're the expert.

733
00:26:20.954 --> 00:26:22.539
I just needed to make sure.

734
00:26:23.957 --> 00:26:25.709
- I was going through
Billings once.

735
00:26:25.793 --> 00:26:29.254
Cop saw my colors.
jacked me up.

736
00:26:29.338 --> 00:26:30.714
kept me overnight.

737
00:26:30.798 --> 00:26:34.384
They threw my sweetheart
in the impound yard.

738
00:26:34.468 --> 00:26:36.261
They claimed
someone backed into it.

739
00:26:36.303 --> 00:26:39.431
but you could see where they
took their hammer to it. man.

740
00:26:39.515 --> 00:26:40.933
You gotta be careful out there.

741
00:26:40.974 --> 00:26:42.267
- This is all pretty minor.
though. right?

742
00:26:42.309 --> 00:26:44.561
- Yeah. shit.
this is just cosmetic.

743
00:26:44.645 --> 00:26:47.064
Bring it in tomorrow.
and we'll get Bonnie right.

744
00:26:47.147 --> 00:26:48.774
- Well. this will bend back.
This will tighten up.

745
00:26:48.816 --> 00:26:50.442
I can do all that myself.
- Jesus. let me do it.

746
00:26:50.526 --> 00:26:51.735
There's no charge.
- What?

747
00:26:51.819 --> 00:26:53.112
You don't owe me anything.
except

748
00:26:53.153 --> 00:26:55.614
take care of yourself
while I'm gone.

749
00:26:55.656 --> 00:26:57.449
- Boy. this record
never stops. huh?

750
00:26:57.533 --> 00:27:00.369
- Nah. it's dance
till you drop!

751
00:27:00.452 --> 00:27:01.870
- Then what?

752
00:27:01.954 --> 00:27:03.956
- Teach the kids the steps
before you do.

753
00:27:03.997 --> 00:27:05.290
- And then what?

754
00:27:05.374 --> 00:27:06.792
- Hope they make it
farther than you.

755
00:27:06.875 --> 00:27:08.460
- Hey. Robby.
you're coming or going?

756
00:27:08.502 --> 00:27:10.254
- I'm going. pretty soon.
What have you got here?

757
00:27:10.337 --> 00:27:13.132
- Lyman Paine. 53. single MVC.

758
00:27:13.215 --> 00:27:14.299
Drove into a telephone pole.

759
00:27:14.383 --> 00:27:15.634
- Passenger space intrusion?

760
00:27:15.676 --> 00:27:16.760
- No. head on.

761
00:27:16.844 --> 00:27:17.761
- Intoxicated?

762
00:27:17.845 --> 00:27:19.680
- No ETOH on his breath.

763
00:27:19.763 --> 00:27:21.473
Either syncope. seizure.

764
00:27:21.557 --> 00:27:23.976
or he just fell asleep
at the wheel.

765
00:27:24.059 --> 00:27:26.019
Airbag deployed.
unconscious at the scene.

766
00:27:26.103 --> 00:27:27.020
but he's waking up.

767
00:27:27.104 --> 00:27:28.522
- BP 140 over 80.

768
00:27:28.605 --> 00:27:30.315
pulse 120. pulse ox 98.

769
00:27:30.399 --> 00:27:31.608
no obvious injuries.

770
00:27:31.692 --> 00:27:32.609
- Why don't you guys
head on in?

771
00:27:32.693 --> 00:27:33.819
I'll meet you in a minute.

772
00:27:38.574 --> 00:27:41.326
Well. hey. buddy.
I guess this is it.

773
00:27:41.368 --> 00:27:43.162
Make those appointments
next week. you know?

774
00:27:43.245 --> 00:27:45.330
I'll call you from the road
to make sure you do.

775
00:27:45.372 --> 00:27:46.999
- Don't do that. man.
- What?

776
00:27:47.040 --> 00:27:48.959
- Don't shine me on.

777
00:27:49.042 --> 00:27:50.919
- I'm not.

778
00:27:51.003 --> 00:27:52.337
- Jesus.

779
00:27:52.421 --> 00:27:54.173
I get it.

780
00:27:54.214 --> 00:27:57.217
Hard place to leave.
a harder place to stay.

781
00:27:58.844 --> 00:28:00.053
- Yeah.

782
00:28:02.389 --> 00:28:05.142
- Look. I'm not ready
to say goodbye yet.

783
00:28:05.225 --> 00:28:08.645
So go do what you gotta do.
and I'll get some tools

784
00:28:08.729 --> 00:28:11.023
from the truck
and see if I can't make

785
00:28:11.064 --> 00:28:13.233
Bonnie smile again for you.

786
00:28:16.904 --> 00:28:18.155
- OK.

787
00:28:18.238 --> 00:28:19.823
- OK. then.

788
00:28:26.830 --> 00:28:29.208
- Robby. man. I'm so sorry.
We've been on for 14 straight.

789
00:28:29.249 --> 00:28:30.834
I thought I cleared it.
- It's all right.

790
00:28:30.918 --> 00:28:32.085
- Honestly. I feel terrible.

791
00:28:32.169 --> 00:28:33.921
- No real harm done.

792
00:28:34.004 --> 00:28:35.714
I was bound to nick it up
on the road anyway.

793
00:28:35.797 --> 00:28:39.051
First blood drawn.
it's a good omen really.

794
00:28:39.092 --> 00:28:40.510
- Thought he'd be more pissed.

795
00:28:40.594 --> 00:28:42.554
- I thought you might
get punched.

796
00:28:42.596 --> 00:28:44.056
- Chest and belly look good.

797
00:28:44.097 --> 00:28:45.390
Let me drag Neurosurgery
down here to deal with

798
00:28:45.432 --> 00:28:46.558
the C-spine before I go.

799
00:28:46.642 --> 00:28:49.061
- You off?
- Yep. an hour ago.

800
00:28:49.144 --> 00:28:51.021
Can't you tell?
- How you doing. sir?

801
00:28:51.104 --> 00:28:53.732
- Actually. not too good.

802
00:28:53.774 --> 00:28:55.067
The tingling is getting worse.

803
00:28:55.108 --> 00:28:56.735
It's in both my arms now.

804
00:28:56.777 --> 00:28:58.362
I feel like something's wrong.

805
00:28:58.445 --> 00:29:00.572
- Hey. man.
What are we looking at?

806
00:29:00.614 --> 00:29:03.200
- Ran into a telephone pole.
airbag deployed.

807
00:29:03.283 --> 00:29:04.743
- Seizure? Stroke?

808
00:29:04.785 --> 00:29:06.078
- Not sure.

809
00:29:06.119 --> 00:29:07.246
Possible C-spine.

810
00:29:07.287 --> 00:29:09.581
CT showed
uni-facet dislocation.

811
00:29:09.665 --> 00:29:11.416
- I'm trying not to freak out.

812
00:29:11.458 --> 00:29:13.001
I'm having trouble breathing.

813
00:29:13.085 --> 00:29:15.087
- Squeeze my hand.

814
00:29:15.170 --> 00:29:16.713
Real hard.

815
00:29:16.797 --> 00:29:17.798
Three out of five strength.

816
00:29:17.881 --> 00:29:18.924
- OK.

817
00:29:19.007 --> 00:29:20.425
10 milligrams dexamethasone.

818
00:29:20.509 --> 00:29:22.594
- Dexamethasone?
For spinal injury?

819
00:29:22.636 --> 00:29:24.137
- It's compression
from a jumped facet

820
00:29:24.221 --> 00:29:25.806
and maybe some ischemia
from a kinked vessel.

821
00:29:25.889 --> 00:29:27.224
- What's--what's happening?

822
00:29:27.307 --> 00:29:29.768
- Sir. you have
a partial dislocation

823
00:29:29.851 --> 00:29:31.395
of two vertebrae in your neck.

824
00:29:31.478 --> 00:29:33.230
It's putting pressure
on your spinal cord.

825
00:29:33.313 --> 00:29:34.815
- How do you fix it?

826
00:29:34.898 --> 00:29:37.609
- We need Neurosurgery
to screw a clamp

827
00:29:37.651 --> 00:29:39.486
into both sides of your skull

828
00:29:39.569 --> 00:29:42.406
and then use traction
under X-ray guidance

829
00:29:42.489 --> 00:29:43.949
to get everything realigned.

830
00:29:43.991 --> 00:29:46.535
- Like a chiropractic
adjustment?

831
00:29:46.618 --> 00:29:49.371
- It's a bit more
complicated than that.

832
00:29:49.454 --> 00:29:51.248
- I think I'm having
a panic attack.

833
00:29:51.331 --> 00:29:54.209
because I can't even get
a shallow breath.

834
00:29:54.293 --> 00:29:56.795
- Or he's losing C3. 4. and 5.

835
00:29:56.837 --> 00:29:58.755
- Uh. page Neurosurgery.

836
00:29:58.839 --> 00:30:00.799
- Garcia went to go get them.
- No. Page overhead.

837
00:30:00.882 --> 00:30:03.468
Find Robby if he's still here.

838
00:30:03.552 --> 00:30:06.305
- Any available neurosurgeon
to ED Trauma 1. stat!

839
00:30:06.346 --> 00:30:09.599
<i>Any available neurosurgeon
to ED Trauma 1. stat!</i>

840
00:30:09.683 --> 00:30:11.310
[liquid trickling]

841
00:30:11.393 --> 00:30:13.312
[knocking on door]
- Dr. Robby?

842
00:30:13.353 --> 00:30:16.648
- Uh. yeah?

843
00:30:16.732 --> 00:30:19.526
[toilet flushes]
- You're needed in Trauma 1.

844
00:30:19.609 --> 00:30:21.320
- OK.

845
00:30:21.403 --> 00:30:22.696
What patient?
- Dr. Langdon's.

846
00:30:22.779 --> 00:30:24.072
It's a neck injury.

847
00:30:27.200 --> 00:30:28.368
- I got the fellow.

848
00:30:28.452 --> 00:30:29.703
They could be down
in 15 minutes.

849
00:30:29.786 --> 00:30:30.996
- He's progressing
too fast for that.

850
00:30:31.038 --> 00:30:32.873
- What's going on?

851
00:30:32.956 --> 00:30:35.459
- Uni-facet dislocation. C4/C5.

852
00:30:35.500 --> 00:30:37.169
paresthesia
and decreased tidal volume.

853
00:30:37.252 --> 00:30:38.503
- Sat's 85.

854
00:30:38.587 --> 00:30:40.505
- We need to prepare
for intubation.

855
00:30:40.547 --> 00:30:42.174
- Any delay in reduction
almost guarantees

856
00:30:42.257 --> 00:30:44.509
complete spinal cord injury.

857
00:30:44.593 --> 00:30:46.511
- What other options
do we have?

858
00:30:46.595 --> 00:30:50.182
- Uh. I saw Neurosurgery do
a closed reduction once in ICU.

859
00:30:50.265 --> 00:30:51.683
- Blind? That's crazy risky.

860
00:30:51.725 --> 00:30:52.976
- We gotta do something.

861
00:30:53.060 --> 00:30:54.519
What's that procedure.
Dr. Langdon?

862
00:30:54.603 --> 00:30:56.688
- It's just--
it's traction on the neck.

863
00:30:56.772 --> 00:30:59.358
we flex the dislocated side
and into slight extension.

864
00:30:59.441 --> 00:31:00.859
- Quadriplegia. if done wrong.

865
00:31:00.901 --> 00:31:02.486
- I'm sorry. what--
did you say quadriplegic?

866
00:31:02.569 --> 00:31:03.987
- It is a possibility. sir.

867
00:31:04.029 --> 00:31:05.822
It's also the same possibility
if we do nothing.

868
00:31:05.906 --> 00:31:07.032
- You wanna try?

869
00:31:07.115 --> 00:31:08.867
- I've never seen it done.
You have.

870
00:31:08.909 --> 00:31:10.327
- I can't feel my feet.

871
00:31:10.410 --> 00:31:11.870
- Sats 79. 100% non-rebreather?

872
00:31:11.912 --> 00:31:13.205
- He's progressing.
Dr. Langdon.

873
00:31:13.246 --> 00:31:14.664
What is your plan?

874
00:31:14.748 --> 00:31:16.166
- Uh. Neuro--

875
00:31:16.208 --> 00:31:17.834
- Fuck Neuro.
This is right here. right now.

876
00:31:17.918 --> 00:31:19.419
This guy's gonna be
a living head if we do nothing.

877
00:31:19.503 --> 00:31:22.089
- I could paralyze him.
- Doctor the fuck up.

878
00:31:22.172 --> 00:31:23.882
[machine beeping]

879
00:31:23.965 --> 00:31:26.385
- [gasping]

880
00:31:26.426 --> 00:31:29.221
- Sir. the partial dislocation
of the two vertebrae

881
00:31:29.304 --> 00:31:31.556
in your neck is putting
pressure on your spinal cord.

882
00:31:31.640 --> 00:31:34.226
I can try to move the neck
bones back into place.

883
00:31:34.267 --> 00:31:36.186
That could help.
There's no guarantees.

884
00:31:36.269 --> 00:31:37.729
If we do nothing.

885
00:31:37.771 --> 00:31:39.398
the weakness is definitely
going to get worse.

886
00:31:39.439 --> 00:31:41.900
But either way. there's still
a chance of paralysis.

887
00:31:41.942 --> 00:31:44.444
- Do it.
Please. Please.

888
00:31:44.528 --> 00:31:46.071
- 50 of fentanyl IV.

889
00:31:46.154 --> 00:31:47.906
You need to let us know
if the weakness gets worse

890
00:31:47.948 --> 00:31:50.200
or if there's any sudden pain.
and we'll stop immediately.

891
00:31:50.283 --> 00:31:51.743
Dr. Cruz. Robby.

892
00:31:51.785 --> 00:31:54.079
hold down his shoulders
for countertraction.

893
00:31:54.121 --> 00:31:56.039
OK. I'm gonna pull
on your head.

894
00:31:56.123 --> 00:31:57.999
Your job is to try to relax.

895
00:31:58.083 --> 00:32:00.419
breathe so we can overcome
the muscle spasm.

896
00:32:00.460 --> 00:32:03.338
[machine beeping]

897
00:32:05.340 --> 00:32:06.883
Flexing to the right.

898
00:32:10.137 --> 00:32:11.346
Any change?

899
00:32:11.430 --> 00:32:13.723
- My legs are starting
to tingle.

900
00:32:13.807 --> 00:32:15.350
- Last step.

901
00:32:18.353 --> 00:32:19.771
[bones crack]
- Ah!

902
00:32:19.855 --> 00:32:20.981
- I felt something click.
- Oh. fuck! Oh. fuck!

903
00:32:21.064 --> 00:32:22.607
- I felt it too.
- Sir. talk to us.

904
00:32:22.649 --> 00:32:24.234
What's going on?
- Oh.

905
00:32:24.317 --> 00:32:26.278
[panting]
I think--

906
00:32:26.319 --> 00:32:27.654
I think...
[laughs]

907
00:32:27.737 --> 00:32:29.781
Yeah.
I'm starting to breathe easier.

908
00:32:29.823 --> 00:32:31.908
- Any change
in your hand or feet?

909
00:32:31.992 --> 00:32:33.410
- Oh.

910
00:32:33.493 --> 00:32:34.786
Oh. this is maybe
a little less numb.

911
00:32:34.828 --> 00:32:36.329
- Philadelphia collar is ready.

912
00:32:36.413 --> 00:32:37.497
- Talk to me.

913
00:32:37.581 --> 00:32:38.790
- Langdon just reduced

914
00:32:38.874 --> 00:32:40.625
a uni-facet
cervical dislocation.

915
00:32:40.709 --> 00:32:43.462
- What? Without neurosurgery?
Don't try this at home. kids.

916
00:32:43.503 --> 00:32:45.005
- He was deteriorating quickly.

917
00:32:45.088 --> 00:32:46.465
- Neuro exam is improving.

918
00:32:46.548 --> 00:32:48.508
- Oh. my God.
it's definitely better.

919
00:32:48.592 --> 00:32:51.344
Oh. my God.

920
00:32:51.428 --> 00:32:53.221
- Nice job.

921
00:32:53.305 --> 00:32:54.639
- All right. repeat CT.

922
00:32:54.723 --> 00:32:56.141
then Neurosurgery
can take him up for a halo.

923
00:32:56.224 --> 00:32:57.476
Brass balls. buddy.

924
00:32:57.559 --> 00:32:59.644
See? You haven't lost it.
- Um. excuse me.

925
00:32:59.686 --> 00:33:02.189
I'm just gonna step outside
for a second.

926
00:33:17.162 --> 00:33:19.831
- Langdon. honey. I just got
a call from upstairs.

927
00:33:19.915 --> 00:33:21.291
Were you supposed to get
a urine screen

928
00:33:21.374 --> 00:33:22.959
and turn it in by 8:00 tonight?
- Fuck!

929
00:33:23.043 --> 00:33:24.169
Um...

930
00:33:25.378 --> 00:33:27.631
Oh. no.
Uh. ye--yes.

931
00:33:27.714 --> 00:33:29.633
Can you just--can you tell them
that I was in a trauma?

932
00:33:29.716 --> 00:33:31.009
I'm going right now.

933
00:33:34.763 --> 00:33:36.223
- Where's he off to?

934
00:33:36.306 --> 00:33:38.016
- No idea.

935
00:33:38.099 --> 00:33:40.560
Did you find your ID badge yet?

936
00:33:40.644 --> 00:33:42.562
- No. I've looked everywhere.

937
00:33:42.646 --> 00:33:44.231
Must have been thrown out
on accident.

938
00:33:44.314 --> 00:33:45.732
- They'll issue you a new one.

939
00:33:45.815 --> 00:33:47.025
You just have to fill out
a bunch of forms.

940
00:33:47.108 --> 00:33:48.527
[notification chimes]
- Oh. great.

941
00:33:52.447 --> 00:33:53.949
What?

942
00:33:54.032 --> 00:33:54.950
- Cow in labor?

943
00:33:55.033 --> 00:33:56.368
- No. I--

944
00:33:56.451 --> 00:33:58.328
I ordered a patient a Lyft.

945
00:33:58.411 --> 00:34:02.791
Now I have a $250 surcharge
and a complaint on my account.

946
00:34:02.874 --> 00:34:04.876
- What?
- What'd they do?

947
00:34:04.960 --> 00:34:06.336
- It was a sweet old lady.

948
00:34:06.419 --> 00:34:08.380
- Who apparently had
some racist

949
00:34:08.463 --> 00:34:10.048
and abusive things to say

950
00:34:10.090 --> 00:34:12.342
right before puking
in the back.

951
00:34:12.425 --> 00:34:15.053
- You never know
with some people.

952
00:34:15.095 --> 00:34:16.388
- There goes my first paycheck.

953
00:34:16.471 --> 00:34:17.889
- St. Huckleberry.

954
00:34:17.931 --> 00:34:19.182
No good deed.

955
00:34:22.143 --> 00:34:25.188
- I can see why you liked
restoring this bike.

956
00:34:25.272 --> 00:34:26.898
You're a fixer.

957
00:34:26.940 --> 00:34:29.025
I fix bikes.
but you fix people.

958
00:34:29.109 --> 00:34:31.695
That's pretty damn
impressive. man.

959
00:34:31.778 --> 00:34:33.738
- Some people can't be fixed.

960
00:34:35.156 --> 00:34:37.367
- Look. I'm--

961
00:34:37.450 --> 00:34:40.370
I've done plenty of things
I'm not proud of.

962
00:34:40.453 --> 00:34:41.371
- Yeah. me too.

963
00:34:41.413 --> 00:34:44.040
- No. bad things--

964
00:34:44.124 --> 00:34:46.585
hurt people on purpose.

965
00:34:46.668 --> 00:34:48.420
hurt myself.

966
00:34:48.461 --> 00:34:51.214
And I did my time. but that
doesn't wash away the regret.

967
00:34:51.298 --> 00:34:53.592
I...

968
00:34:53.633 --> 00:34:55.885
wish I'd done things
differently.

969
00:34:55.969 --> 00:34:58.346
I think about it every day.

970
00:34:58.430 --> 00:35:01.516
- You know. they say that
it's never too late to change.

971
00:35:01.600 --> 00:35:05.228
- Some things can't be changed.
like death.

972
00:35:05.312 --> 00:35:07.063
Death can't be changed.

973
00:35:07.147 --> 00:35:08.940
- Hey. I know
the surgery is scary.

974
00:35:09.024 --> 00:35:11.693
- I'm not talking about me.

975
00:35:25.498 --> 00:35:28.543
- Yeah. I don't know if
I wanna be here anymore.

976
00:35:30.545 --> 00:35:32.839
- I don't know how you stand
12 minutes in there.

977
00:35:32.922 --> 00:35:37.469
let alone 12 hours. 20 years.

978
00:35:37.552 --> 00:35:38.803
- No.

979
00:35:38.845 --> 00:35:41.139
That's the only place I can be.

980
00:35:41.222 --> 00:35:46.353
I have purpose in there.
I can be distracted in there.

981
00:35:46.436 --> 00:35:50.148
I don't know that I wanna be...

982
00:35:50.190 --> 00:35:54.027
anywhere anymore.

983
00:35:54.110 --> 00:35:56.112
[exhales]

984
00:35:59.032 --> 00:36:01.451
- So what's the plan?

985
00:36:01.534 --> 00:36:04.079
[distant sirens wailing]
- Ride.

986
00:36:04.162 --> 00:36:05.955
- Toward what?
- I don't know.

987
00:36:06.039 --> 00:36:07.082
- Away from what?

988
00:36:07.165 --> 00:36:09.000
- Everything.

989
00:36:09.084 --> 00:36:12.253
- Well. that's not riding.
That's running.

990
00:36:12.337 --> 00:36:15.382
Is that your final lesson
for these kids?

991
00:36:20.553 --> 00:36:22.013
- What's up. Robby?

992
00:36:22.055 --> 00:36:25.725
- Well. if it isn't
Medics Bosco and Otero.

993
00:36:27.894 --> 00:36:28.937
- You still on?

994
00:36:29.020 --> 00:36:30.146
- Not for much longer.

995
00:36:30.230 --> 00:36:32.482
I was looking for you two.

996
00:36:32.565 --> 00:36:34.150
- Rita Wolcott. 22.

997
00:36:34.234 --> 00:36:36.361
She was using a dumpster
to climb a fire escape

998
00:36:36.403 --> 00:36:37.862
to get to a roof party.

999
00:36:37.904 --> 00:36:39.698
Slipped about 6 feet
onto concrete.

1000
00:36:39.739 --> 00:36:41.324
Possible tib-fib fracture.

1001
00:36:41.408 --> 00:36:42.701
- Oh. can I please tell it?

1002
00:36:42.742 --> 00:36:44.411
You're making me sound
like an idiot.

1003
00:36:44.494 --> 00:36:46.037
My friends and I were just
trying to watch the fireworks

1004
00:36:46.121 --> 00:36:47.539
from the roof of our building.

1005
00:36:47.580 --> 00:36:49.708
But the roof access door
and the stairwells stuck.

1006
00:36:49.749 --> 00:36:51.918
so we decided to climb
the fire escape.

1007
00:36:52.001 --> 00:36:53.962
They were supposed to hold
the dumpster still while I...

1008
00:36:54.671 --> 00:36:55.714
But they didn't.

1009
00:36:55.797 --> 00:36:57.090
Then I fell.

1010
00:36:57.173 --> 00:36:59.259
- Like I said.
6 feet onto concrete.

1011
00:36:59.342 --> 00:37:01.302
- Yeah. because they didn't
hold it still.

1012
00:37:01.386 --> 00:37:02.887
- Well. it's a good thing
she didn't need a 12-lead.

1013
00:37:02.929 --> 00:37:04.639
- Why's that?

1014
00:37:04.723 --> 00:37:05.974
- 'Cause you guys put one on
about a half hour ago wrong

1015
00:37:06.057 --> 00:37:07.183
and you missed the STEMI.

1016
00:37:07.267 --> 00:37:08.184
- Bullshit.

1017
00:37:08.268 --> 00:37:09.352
- 46-year-old woman.

1018
00:37:09.436 --> 00:37:11.146
A minute after you left.
V-tach.

1019
00:37:11.229 --> 00:37:13.523
Repeat EKG showed
a massive lateral STEMI.

1020
00:37:13.606 --> 00:37:14.733
- No way.

1021
00:37:14.774 --> 00:37:16.192
- Leads were so inferior.

1022
00:37:16.276 --> 00:37:17.819
you might as well
have not put them on at all.

1023
00:37:17.902 --> 00:37:19.362
What were you afraid of.
